## 1. What this project is

{{ project_description or project_name + " — a backend service." }}

More than that, it's a project built on one core idea:

> **The AI writes and ships most of the code, and a human does not review every line.
> So the safety rails — not the code — are the real product.**

Everything unusual here exists to make that safe: automatic checks that **fail closed** (when
in doubt, they stop rather than let something risky through), and rules that an AI assistant
*cannot quietly switch off* to make its work pass. The full reasoning is written down in
[`decisions/0004-agent-resistant-guardrails.md`](decisions/0004-agent-resistant-guardrails.md).

**Why this matters to you:** you don't have to personally catch every mistake. If you (or the
AI) do something unsafe, a check is designed to catch it. Your job is to understand *what the
checks protect*, so you can make good decisions — not to memorize the code.

