## 3. The three rules — and why they exist

These are the non-negotiables from [`CLAUDE.md`](../CLAUDE.md). If you understand nothing else,
understand these:

1. **Secrets never go into the project's history.** Passwords, keys, and tokens stay out of the
   code. *Why:* once a secret is committed it's effectively public forever, even if deleted.
2. **When something is unclear or missing, stop — don't guess around it.** A missing key or an
   unclear permission makes the system *deny*, not quietly continue in an unsafe way. *Why:* a
   silent unsafe fallback is how real breaches happen.
3. **Never weaken a check to make something pass.** If a guard blocks you, fix the underlying
   problem. *Why:* the guards are the product — disabling one removes the protection you're
   relying on. (An AI assistant is explicitly instructed to fix the code, not the check.)

