## 4. Your day-to-day loop

You mostly work through an AI assistant. After any change, the routine is:

```bash
make check        # runs all the automated checks locally
make dod-check    # checks the docs still match the code
```

If those are green and the docs are updated, you're done. The full "**Definition of Done**"
ritual (what to update after each change) is in [`CLAUDE.md`](../CLAUDE.md) §2 — the AI follows
it for you, but it's good to know it exists.

To turn the repo's server-side protections on (a one-time step), follow
[`ONBOARDING.md`](../ONBOARDING.md).

